as set forth in the FDCA and applicable regulations promulgated thereunder (including, for example, 21 C.F.R. Parts 50, 54, and 56),
as amended from time to time, and such standards of good clinical practice (including all applicable requirements relating to protection
of human subjects) as are required by any Governmental Body in any other countries, including applicable regulations or guidelines from
the International Conference on Harmonisation of Technical Requirements for Registration of Pharmaceuticals for Human Use, in which the
Company Products are distributed, sold or intended to be sold, to the extent such standards are not less stringent than in the United
States.</P>

